This is a jQuery plugin providing 'Twitter widget'.
'twitterWidget()' method that loads and displays tweets based on the properties provided below;

[Properties]
screen_name: The screen name of the target user / ex: 'twitterapi'
count: number Specifies the number of tweets to try and retrieve, up to a maximum of 200 / ex: 100
speed: Interval (seconds) / ex: 10
exclude_replies: Prevent replies from appearing in the returned timeline / true or false
include_rts: The timeline will strip any native retweets / true or false
dateformat: Format of date / ex: 'Y/M/D h:m:s'
path: Path to 'twitter.php' / ex: './api/'
src: Source of each parts
src.header: Header source / ex: "<span>$screen_name$</span>"
src.body: Main source / ex: "<span>$text$</span><span>$created_at$</span>"
src.footer: Footer source / ex: "<span>$logo$</span>"
src.reply: Reply button source / ex: "Re:"
src.retweet: Retweet button source / ex: "RT"
src.favorite: Favorite button source / ex: "<img src='./images/favorite.png' alt='' title'' />"

[Reserved words]
$icon$: User icon
$screen_name$: Screen name
$name$: Display name
$description$: Description of user profile (includes 'URL', when the user defines).
$text$: Tweet text
$created_at$: Date
$logo$: Twitter logo
$reply$: Reply button
$retweet$: Retweet button
$favorite$: Favorite button
$action$: Includes $reply$, $retweet$, and $favorite$.


Here's a specific example;

[html]
<div id="twitter"></div>

[twitter.php]
Uploading 'twitter.php' to the installed directory is required.

[jQuery]
$(function() {
	var option = {
		screen_name: 'twitterapi',
		speed: 10,
		exclude_replies: true,
		include_rts: false,
		dateformat: 'Y/M/D h:m:s',
		path: './api/',
		src: {
			header: "<div class='clearfix'><strong>$icon$</strong><span>$screen_name$</span><span>($name$)</span></div><p>$description$</p>",
			body: "<div class='tw'><span class='tw_text'>$text$</span> <span class='tw_date'>$created_at$</span><div>$action$</div></div>",
			footer: "<div class='clearfix'>$logo$<span>Twitter</span></div>",
			reply: "<img src='./reply.png' alt='' title='' />",
			retweet: "<img src='./retweet.png' alt='' title='' />",
			favorite: "<img src='./favorite.png' alt='' title='' />"
		}
	};
	$('#twitter').twitterWidget(option);
});

Hope this helps and thanks for reading!
